Two people have died in a road accident along the Kangundo-Kathiani road in Machakos county on Saturday. The accident occurred after a Truck collided head on with a motorbike and killed two on the spot. Among the dead is the motorbike driver and a customer. Kangundo County police commander Benjamin O'ngombe said the truck which was ferrying sand to Kathiani was speeding and lost control. The truck driver and his turnboy have been arrested and taken to Kangundo Police station.